      <ProductCard href="https://amzn.to/3Q3Omob">
        <a
          href="https://www.amazon.com/Atomic-Habits-Proven-Build-Break/dp/0735211299?_encoding=UTF8&qid=1696433289&sr=1-1&linkCode=li3&tag=selfimprovi09-20&linkId=91935faf07c325f0f28a4564a99df170&language=en_US&ref_=as_li_ss_il"
          target="_blank"
          rel="nofollow"
          ><img
            width="165"
            height="250"
            src="https://ws-na.amazon-adsystem.com/widgets/q?_encoding=UTF8&ASIN=0735211299&Format=_SL250_&ID=AsinImage&MarketPlace=US&ServiceVersion=20070822&WS=1&tag=selfimprovi09-20&language=en_US"
            alt="Atomic Habits by James Clear"
          /></a
        >
      </ProductCard>
    </div>

    <BooksQuote
      quote="You do not rise to the level of your goals. You fall to the level of your systems."
    />

    <h3 class="!mt-6 link--theme">Summary:</h3>
    <p>
      "Atomic Habits" is a transformative guide that explores the science of
      habit formation. Clear offers practical strategies to make small changes
      that can lead to remarkable personal and professional growth.
    </p>

    <h3 class="link--theme">What It Teaches:</h3>
    <p>
      "Atomic Habits" teaches readers how to harness the power of small habits
      to achieve long-term success. It emphasizes the importance of
      understanding habit cues, cravings, responses, and rewards to create
      meaningful and lasting behavioral change.
    </p>

    <h3 class="link--theme">Amazon Review:</h3>
    <p class="text-sm">
      "I can only recommend it to people that want to build good habits and get
      rid of bad ones. A good read and step by step explanation of the core
      principles a habit is made out of"
    </p>

